// ══ ONCLICK -> ADDEVENTLISTENER WIRING (static markup only) ══
// Generated by converting onclick="EXPR" attributes on fixed markup
// elements into addEventListener calls. An inline onclick="EXPR" is
// exactly equivalent to el.addEventListener('click', function(event){
// EXPR }) -- both bind `this` to the element and expose `event` in
// scope -- so this preserves behavior exactly rather than changing it.
//
// Scope: only elements present in the initial HTML. Elements rendered
// dynamically via template literals (menu items, coupons, stock rows,
// etc.) still use inline onclick -- converting those requires rewriting
// each render function to use event delegation instead, which is a
// separate, larger change.
